> @wangxianghu as discussed, I have done the required changes. Here, I have reverted the changes done for spark-utilities module, I will start the discussion on it on mail thread.

@veenaypatil how about the tests?
have you tested the jars on cluster dev

@satishkotha Couple of high level questions:
* Would preserving commit time be sufficient to support incremental read? Won't we need incremental timeline support (#2388 ) as well? 
* I see that a new `SparkAllowUpdateStrategy` has been added. How are we handling update conflicts?

@codope 
I have added the tests for both `INSER_OVERWRITE` and `INSERT_OVERWRITE_TABLE` .
please review ^

@leesf Just realized this PR changed the layout of the page completely as well. Could we discuss such large changes bit more? :) My bad for not catching this. This title gave me the impression that its just fixing some docs. 

One ability we lost here, is the linking directly to a config. This is very very useful in answering questions or pointing users in the right direction. Also not sure table is actually easier to read. you have to really scroll a lot horizontally (even on a 32" monitor) to read this. 

Can we please go back to the list we had before and discuss this more?

@zhangyue19921010 no worries. I really appreciate the efforts you took! 

Personally, I am not convinced the table is necessarily a better approach actually. The horizontal scrolling can be very detrimental to easy reading, right? That said, the current docs are written with references to the builder pattern used by writeconfig etc, which was not great either. 

So lets work together to improve this. What parts of the previous config layout did you want to change the most.
